        <p class="PublicationsDetailBold">
            <p class="PublicationsDetailNormal">
                <span id="ContentPlaceHolder1_LinkPaperPage_LinkPaperContent_LabelAbstractTitle" class="LabelSearchRepeater">Abstract: </span>

                <span id="ContentPlaceHolder1_LinkPaperPage_LinkPaperContent_LabelAbstract">The proliferation of electronic health databases has resulted in the existence of a wide collection of diversified
clinical digital data. These data are fragmented over dispersed databases in different clinical silos around the
world. The exploration of these electronic health records (EHRs) is essential for clinical and pharmaceutical
research and, therefore, solutions for secure sharing of information across different databases are needed.
Although several partial solutions have been proposed over the years, data sharing and integration has been
hindered by many ethical, legal and social issues. In this paper, we present a methodology to perform semi-automatic
queries over longitudinal clinical data repositories, where every data custodian maintains full control
of data.</span>
                <span id="ContentPlaceHolder1_LinkPaperPage_LinkPaperContent_MoreAbstract" class="lessAbstract" style="transition: 0.5s all; margin-left: -3px;"></span>

                

                
                    <script type="text/javascript">
                        function CollapseExpandAbstract(description) {
                            var option = document.getElementById(description.id).textContent;

                            var label = document.getElementById('ContentPlaceHolder1_LinkPaperPage_LinkPaperContent_MoreAbstract');
                            if (option == "(More)") {
                                label.className = "moreAbstract";
                                document.getElementById(description.id).textContent = "(Less)";
                            }
                            if (option == "(Less)") {
                                label.className = "lessAbstract";
                                document.getElementById(description.id).textContent = "(More)";
                            }

                        }
                    </script>
                

                
                <div id="ctl00_ContentPlaceHolder1_LinkPaperPage_LinkPaperContent_RadToolTip1" style="display:none;position:absolute;">
	
                    <span id="ContentPlaceHolder1_LinkPaperPage_LinkPaperContent_LabelAbstractPopUp" style="font-size: 14px;"></span>
                <input id="ctl00_ContentPlaceHolder1_LinkPaperPage_LinkPaperContent_RadToolTip1_ClientState" name="ctl00_ContentPlaceHolder1_LinkPaperPage_LinkPaperContent_RadToolTip1_ClientState" type="hidden" />
</div>
                
            </p>
        </p>

